{{confused|Sociedad Anónima Deportiva}} {{Companies law}} '''Sociedade Anónima Desportiva''' ("Public limited sports company") is a special type of [[public limited company]] ([[S.A. (corporation)|SA]]) in [[Portugal]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Decreto Lei nº 10/ 2013, 25 January|url=http://dre.pt/pdf1sdip/2013/01/01800/0050500509.pdf|work=Official publisher of Assembly Republic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Decreto Lei 67/97, 3 of April|url=http://www.dre.pt/pdf1s/1997/04/078A00/14891493.pdf|work=Official publisher of Assembly Republic}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sociedades desportivas|url=http://www.parlamento.pt/Legislacao/Paginas/Desporto_Sociedadesdesportivas.aspx|work=parlamento.pt}}</ref> The new legal status was introduced in the early 1990s to improve financial management and transparency in [[sports clubs]]. Many Portuguese [[Association football|football]] and [[basketball]] clubs add the suffix '''S.A.D.''' to the end of their official name.
