In [[finance]], a '''structurer''' is a person who designs [[structured product]]s and determines how the pay rules will distribute [[cash flow]]s for a deal.  Structurers will also typically build [[Computer simulation|computer model]]s to mimic the pay rules in order to see how collateral payments affect the bond payments. 
All the above should be done before a deal settles, afterward it should be in the hands of the Bond administration to apply the rules as described in the deal [[Legal instrument|legal document]]s.

